  <div data-component="article-content">


            <p>We still don't know much about <a href="https://www.eurogamer.net/games/gears-of-war-e-day">Gears of War: E-Day</a>, but that's set to change next month, when the cover-based third-person shooter prequel gets <a href="https://www.eurogamer.net/xbox-games-showcase-2026-time-date">its own time to shine directly after the next  Xbox Games Showcase 2026</a>. However, we might have learned about the potential release window earlier than intended.</p>
<p>WWE subsidiary <a href="https://x.com/luchalibreaaa/status/2053259088146862285?s=20">Lucha Libre AAA Worldwide's X account</a> (hat tip to <a href="https://www.gamesradar.com/games/gears-of-war/gears-of-war-e-day-is-officially-sponsoring-wwe-triplemania-potentially-hinting-at-a-september-release-date-window-for-the-xbox-prequel/">GamesRadar</a>) announced on 10th May the two-night WWE Triplemania 34 event, which is coming to Ciudad de México and another city that hasn't been revealed yet. The 34-second spot is squarely focused on the event, but its ending stretch shows Gears of War: E-Day's logo, confirming the game as one of its bigger sponsors. The event will take place on 11th and 13th September.</p>

<figure>
<p>
