<figcaption>Gears of War E-Day - Official Reveal Trailer<a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=-L5dMhhnNCw" rel="noopener" target="_blank">Watch on YouTube</a></figcaption></figure>


<p>Of course, a WWE Triplemania advert alone doesn't confirm anything, and even if marketing has ramped up by September, the game could still arrive later. That said, the timing of E-Day's big showcase suggests Xbox may be committing to a release later in 2026, and with <a href="https://www.eurogamer.net/games/grand-theft-auto-vi">GTA 6</a>'s shadow covering November, it seems logical to release the next Gears of War before it.</p><p>A September release window would also make the month an extremely busy one, with other triple-A releases like <a href="https://www.eurogamer.net/blood-of-dawnwalker-release-date">The Blood of Dawnwalker</a> and <a href="https://www.eurogamer.net/ps5-exclusive-marvels-wolverine-claws-its-way-to-a-surprisingly-early-autumn-release-date">Marvel's Wolverine</a> rushing to do their thing before the world belongs to Take-Two and <a href="https://www.eurogamer.net/companies/rockstar-games">Rockstar Games</a>. Gears of War: E-Day should be an easy sell, in any case, as fans have been clamouring for a return to the series' original vibes even if that comes at the expense of setting <a href="https://www.eurogamer.net/games/gears-5">Gears 5</a>'s cliffhanger aside for too long.</p>

